Package controller

Class MainController

  • java.lang.Object
    • controller.Controller
      • controller.WindowController
        • controller.MainController
  • public class MainController
extends WindowController
    Manages the main window that opens after logging in. It provides tabs for the different views and a user menu at the upper-right for logging out or exiting the application. It delegates to other controllers to manage each tab.
    Author:
    Joseph T. Lapp

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        public void initialize()
        Initializes the scene controls for the main window and constructs all of its tabs. Ensures that every time a user selects a new tab, the data displayed in the new tab is fresh.

        LAMBDA - This lambda replaces what would have been another method and passing a reference to that method instead of passing this lambda. The lambda prevents me from having to write that method. In addition to requiring less code, the lambda code is clearer, because the lambda presents the event behavior directly alongside the object to which it responds (tabPane).

      • setContext
